<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt;" align="justify"></p>

<table style="margin-top:3pt; margin-left:0pt; margin-bottom:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;" frame="box" width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
<tr>
<td style="background-color: #D9EBF6">
<p style="margin-top:32pt; margin-bottom:16pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:35pt; font-family:Arial; font-weight:bold; font-size:36pt;" align="left">Notice of 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting </p>
</td>
</tr>
</table>

<p style=" margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:10pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:20pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">Friday, June&nbsp;7,&nbsp;2013 </p>

<p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:17pt; font-weight:bold;/>">7:00&nbsp;a.m., Central time </p>

<p style="margin-top:8pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; />">Bud Walton Arena, University of Arkansas Campus, Fayetteville, Arkansas </p>

<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">Please join us for the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting of Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. to be held on Friday, June&nbsp;7,&nbsp;2013, at&nbsp;7:00&nbsp;a.m., Central time in Bud Walton Arena on the campus of the University of Arkansas, Fayetteville, Arkansas. The&nbsp;purposes of the meeting are: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -18pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">1.</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 25pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
	to elect as directors the 14 nominees identified in the accompanying proxy statement;
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -18pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">2.</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 25pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
	to ratify the appointment of Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP as the company&rsquo;s independent accountants for the fiscal year ending January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2014;
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -18pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">3.</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 25pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
	to vote on a non-binding advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s named executive officers as disclosed in the accompanying proxy statement;
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -18pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">4.</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 25pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
	to vote on the approval of the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Management Incentive Plan, as amended;
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -18pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">5.</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 25pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
	to vote on the four shareholder proposals described in the accompanying proxy statement, if properly presented at the meeting; and
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -18pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">6.</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 25pt; line-height: 18pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 12pt;">
	to transact other business properly brought before the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.
</p>

<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Only shareholders of record as of the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013, the record date for the meeting, are entitled to notice of, and to vote at, the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</i>
</b>
<b></b>If you plan to attend the meeting, please see page&nbsp;14 for information regarding what you must bring with you to gain admittance to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">Regardless of whether you plan to attend, we urge all shareholders to vote on the matters described in the accompanying proxy statement. Please see our questions and answers on page&nbsp;12 for information about voting by mail, telephone, the internet, mobile device, or in person at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Voting in any of the ways described will not prevent you from attending the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">The proxy statement and our Annual Report to Shareholders for the fiscal year ended January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013 are available in the &ldquo;Investors&rdquo; section of our corporate website at <i>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports. </i>

</p>

<p style="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:6pt;padding-left:8.5pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">April&nbsp;22,&nbsp;2013 </p>

<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">Bentonville, Arkansas </p>

<a name="_N1022A"></a>
<div style="padding:6pt; border:1.5pt solid #007DC3;">
<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">Proxy Statement Summary</font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<i>You have received these proxy materials because the Board is soliciting your proxy to vote your Shares at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. This summary highlights information contained elsewhere in this proxy statement. This summary does not contain all of the information that you should consider, and you should read the entire proxy statement carefully before voting. Page references (&ldquo;XX&rdquo;) are supplied to help you find further information in this proxy statement. Please refer to the Table of Abbreviations on page&nbsp;9 when reading this proxy summary. This proxy statement and the related proxy materials were first mailed to shareholders and made available on the internet on April 22, 2013. </i>

</p>

<a name="_N10230"></a>

<p style="margin-top:26pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Time: </b>June&nbsp;7,&nbsp;2013, 7:00&nbsp;a.m., Central time </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Place: </b>Bud Walton Arena, University of Arkansas Campus, Fayetteville, Arkansas 72701 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Record Date: </b>You can vote if you were a shareholder of record at the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013 (page&nbsp;10). </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Admission:</b> You must have proof of ownership as of the Record Date to attend the Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting (page&nbsp;14). </p>

<a name="_N10242"></a>

<p style="margin-top:26pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">Voting Matters and Board Recommendations </p>

<font color="#007DC3">AGAINST</font>
</b>

</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="122.83464566929148" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:bottom;" valign="">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Board is not aware of any matter that will be presented for a vote at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting other than those shown above. </p>

<a name="_N102D7"></a>

<p style="margin-top:26pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">How to Cast Your Vote (page&nbsp;12) </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">You can vote by any of the following methods: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">via the internet <i>(www.proxyvote.com)</i> until 11:59&nbsp;p.m. Eastern time on June&nbsp;6,&nbsp;2013*; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">via telephone by calling 1-800-690-6903 until 11:59&nbsp;p.m. Eastern time on June&nbsp;6,&nbsp;2013*; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">if you received a proxy card or voting instruction form in the mail, by completing, signing, dating, and returning your proxy card or voting instruction form in the return envelope provided to you in accordance with the instructions provided with the proxy card or voting instruction form; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">by scanning the QR code on your proxy card, notice of availability, or voting instruction form with your mobile device; or </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">in person, at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. You must bring proof of ownership of Shares as of the record date in order to attend the Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. See page&nbsp;14 for a description of acceptable forms of proof of Share ownership. If your Shares are held in the name of a broker, nominee, or other intermediary, you must also bring a proxy from the record holder of your Shares as of the record date in order to vote your Shares at the meeting. </p>
<br><br>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">* If your Shares are held through a Walmart 401(k) plan, earlier voting deadlines apply. </p>
</div>

<a name="_N10853"></a>
<div style="padding:6pt; border:1.5pt solid #007DC3;">
<p style="margin-top:26pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">Fiscal 2013 Business Highlights </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Our company had good financial performance in fiscal 2013, particularly with respect to our financial priorities of growth, leverage, and returns. Highlights include: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">diluted earnings per share from continuing operations attributable to Walmart (&ldquo;EPS&rdquo;) increased 10.6% over the prior fiscal year; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">the Walmart U.S. and Sam&rsquo;s Club segments delivered positive comparable store sales; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">we once again leveraged expenses, with sales growing faster than operating expenses; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">our stock price increased approximately 14% during fiscal 2013, and we paid $1.59 per share in dividends; and </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">we announced in February&nbsp;2013 that our Board approved an 18% increase in our annual dividend for fiscal 2014 to $1.88 per share. </p>

<a name="_N10861"></a>

<p style="margin-top:26pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">Fiscal 2013 Executive Compensation Highlights (page&nbsp;40) </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Our executive compensation program is intended to: provide fair, competitive compensation based on performance and contributions to the company; provide incentives to attract and retain key executives; instill a long-term commitment to the company; and encourage company ownership and align the interests of our key executives with the interests of our shareholders, with the ultimate goal of driving long-term shareholder value. With these objectives in mind, our executive compensation program includes the following key features: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">on average, more than 50% of our NEOs&rsquo; target total direct compensation, or TDC, consists of long-term performance shares, and at least 70% of each NEO&rsquo;s target TDC is tied to performance; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">we seek to mitigate risk by using a combination of performance measures, and by capping maximum payouts tied to each performance measure; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">we do not have employment contracts with our Executive Officers. All of our Executive Officers are employed on an &ldquo;at-will&rdquo; basis; and </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">we provide only a limited number of perquisites to our Executive Officers. </p>

<a name="_N1086D"></a>

<p style="margin-top:26pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:16pt; font-weight:bold; color: #007DC3">Primary Components of Our Fiscal 2013 Executive Compensation Program (page&nbsp;44) </p>



<table style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" align="center" width="100%" cellpadding="2" frame="void">
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="143.43307086614175" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;" valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="left">
<b>Component</b>
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="62.36220472440935" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;" valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="left">
<b>Form</b>
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="817.5685039370085" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;" valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="left">
<b>Key Features</b>
</p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="143.43307086614175" style="background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Base Salary</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="62.36220472440935" style="background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Cash</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="817.5685039370085" style="background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Intended to attract and retain top talent </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Generally positioned near the 50<sup>th</sup>&nbsp;percentile of our peer groups, but varies with individual skills, experience, responsibilities, and individual performance </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Represents a relatively small&nbsp;percentage of NEO target TDC</p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="143.43307086614175" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Annual Incentive</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="62.36220472440935" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Cash</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="817.5685039370085" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Tied to operating income performance </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Performance goals established at the beginning of each fiscal year </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Payouts range from 37.5% of target payout to 125% of target payout, depending on performance </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Intended to motivate annual performance with respect to a key financial measure </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Represents approximately 19% - 23% of each NEO&rsquo;s target TDC for fiscal 2013</p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="143.43307086614175" style="background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Performance Shares</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="62.36220472440935" style="background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Equity</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="817.5685039370085" style="background-color:#D9EBF6; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Tied to return on investment and sales performance over a three-year period </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Performance goals established at the beginning of each fiscal year </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Payouts range from 50% of target payout to 150% of target payout, depending on performance </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Intended to motivate long-term performance with respect to key financial measures and align our NEOs&rsquo; interests with those of our shareholders </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Represents 75% of each annual equity grant and approximately 47% - 54% of each NEO&rsquo;s target TDC for fiscal 2013</p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="143.43307086614175" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Restricted Stock</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="62.36220472440935" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">Equity</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="817.5685039370085" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:baseline;" valign="">

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Vests on the third anniversary of grant </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Intended to align our NEOs&rsquo; interests with those of our shareholders and promote retention </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 0pt; padding-left: 9pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify">Represents 25% of each annual equity grant and approximately 16% - 18% of each NEO&rsquo;s target TDC for fiscal 2013</p>

</td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The following abbreviations are used for certain terms that appear in this proxy statement: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>2012 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting:</u> Walmart&rsquo;s Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting held on June&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2012 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting</u>: Walmart&rsquo;s Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting to be held on June&nbsp;7,&nbsp;2013 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>401(k) Plan</u>: the Walmart 401(k) Plan </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Annual Report to Shareholders</u>: Walmart&rsquo;s Annual Report to Shareholders for fiscal 2013 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Associate</u>: an employee of Walmart or one of its subsidiaries </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Audit Committee</u>: the Audit Committee of the Board </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Board</u>: the Board of Directors of Walmart </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Board committees</u>: the Audit Committee, the CNGC, the Executive Committee, the Global Compensation Committee, the SPFC, and the TeCC </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Broadridge</u>: Broadridge Financial Solutions,&nbsp;Inc., representatives of which will serve as the inspectors of election at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Bylaws</u>: the amended and restated Bylaws of Walmart, effective as of June&nbsp;2,&nbsp;2011 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>CD&amp;A</u>: the Compensation Discussion and Analysis included in this proxy statement </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>CEO</u>: the Chief Executive Officer of a company </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>CFO</u>: the Chief Financial Officer of a company </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>CNGC</u>: the Compensation, Nominating and Governance Committee of the Board </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Deferred Compensation Matching Plan</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Deferred Compensation Matching Plan, as adopted effective February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2012, and which replaced the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Director Compensation Deferral Plan</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Director Compensation Deferral Plan, effective June&nbsp;4,&nbsp;2010, which sets forth terms and procedures with respect to the deferral of cash and equity compensation paid to Non-Management Directors </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>E&amp;Y</u>: Ernst&nbsp;&amp; Young LLP, an independent registered public accounting firm </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Exchange Act</u>: the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Executive Committee</u>: the Executive Committee of the Board </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Executive Officers</u>: those senior officers of our company designated by the Board as executive officers (as defined by&nbsp;Rule&nbsp;3b-7 under the Exchange Act) as to whom Walmart has certain disclosure obligations and who must report certain transactions in equity securities of our company under Section&nbsp;16 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Fiscal 2015, fiscal 2014, fiscal 2013, fiscal 2012, fiscal 2011,</u> and <u>fiscal 2010</u>: Walmart&rsquo;s fiscal years ending January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2015,&nbsp;2014,&nbsp;2013,&nbsp;2012,&nbsp;2011, and 2010, respectively </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>GAAP</u>: generally accepted accounting principles in effect in the United&nbsp;States from time to time </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Global Compensation Committee</u> or <u>GCC</u>: the Global Compensation Committee of the Board </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Independent Directors</u>: the Walmart directors whom the Board has determined have no material relationships with our company pursuant to the standards set forth in the NYSE Listed Company Rules and, as to members of the Audit Committee, who meet the requirements of Section&nbsp;10A of the Exchange Act and Rule&nbsp;10A-3 under the Exchange Act and, as to members of the CNGC, who meet the requirements of Section 10C of the Exchange Act and Rule 10C-1 under the Exchange Act </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Internal Revenue Code</u>: the Internal Revenue Code of 1986, as amended </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Management Incentive Plan</u> or <u>MIP</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Management Incentive Plan, as amended and restated effective February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2008; the MIP is being submitted to shareholders for approval, inclusive of recent amendments, at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting (the &ldquo;Amended MIP&rdquo;) </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Named Executive Officers</u> or <u>NEOs</u>: Walmart&rsquo;s President and CEO, Walmart&rsquo;s CFO, and the three most highly compensated Executive Officers other than our CEO and CFO during fiscal 2013 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Non-Management Directors</u>: the members of the Board who are not employed by Walmart or a subsidiary of Walmart </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>NYSE</u>: the New York Stock Exchange </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>NYSE Listed Company Rules</u>: the NYSE&rsquo;s rules for companies with securities listed for trading on the NYSE, including the continual listing requirements and rules and policies on matters such as corporate governance, shareholder communication, and shareholder approval </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Officer Deferred Compensation Plan</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Officer Deferred Compensation Plan, amended and restated effective January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2009, and which was replaced, effective February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2012, with the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>SEC</u>: the Securities and Exchange Commission </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Section&nbsp;16</u>: Section&nbsp;16 of the Exchange Act </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>SERP</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Supplemental Executive Retirement Plan, as&nbsp;amended and restated effective January&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2009, which was replaced, effective February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2012, with the Walmart Deferred Compensation Matching Plan </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Share</u> or <u>Shares</u>: a share or shares of Walmart common stock, $0.10 par value per share </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>SOX</u>: the Sarbanes-Oxley Act of 2002 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>SPFC</u>: the Strategic Planning and Finance Committee of the Board </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Stock Incentive Plan</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Stock Incentive Plan of 2010, as amended </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Stock Purchase Plan</u>: the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. 2004 Associate Stock Purchase Plan, as restated effective February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2004, and subsequently amended </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>TeCC</u>: the Technology and eCommerce Committee of the Board </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<u>Walmart, our company, the company, &ldquo;we,&rdquo; &ldquo;our,&rdquo;</u> or <u>&ldquo;us&rdquo;</u>: Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc., a Delaware corporation and, where the context requires, its consolidated subsidiaries </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">

<a name="_N109BE"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:30pt;padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:27pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">

QUESTIONS AND ANSWERS ABOUT THE MEETING AND&nbsp;VOTING

</font>
</p>

<a name="_N109C1"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">1.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What is a proxy statement and what is a proxy?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">A proxy statement is a document that SEC rules require us to provide you when we ask you to vote on certain matters yourself or when we ask you to sign a proxy designating certain individuals to vote on those matters on your behalf. A proxy is your legal designation of another person to vote the Shares you own. If you designate someone as your proxy in a written document, that document is called a proxy or a proxy card. By signing a proxy card, you will designate our Chairman and our CEO as your proxies to cast your vote at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Walmart&rsquo;s Board is soliciting your proxy to vote your Shares at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Walmart pays the cost of soliciting your proxy and reimburses brokers and others for forwarding to you the proxy statement, proxy card, or voting instruction form, and Annual Report to Shareholders and, for certain shareholders, the notice of internet availability of our proxy materials. </p>

<a name="_N109C8"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">2.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
Who may vote at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">You may vote at the meeting if you were the holder of record of Shares at the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013. You are entitled to one vote on each matter presented at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting for each Share you owned at that time. Some shareholders hold shares through a bank, broker, or other nominee, and are often said to hold such shares in &ldquo;street name.&rdquo;  These shareholders are considered &ldquo;beneficial owners&rdquo; of those Shares. If you held Shares as a beneficial owner in &ldquo;street name&rdquo; at the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013, you must obtain a legal proxy, executed in your favor, from the holder of record of those Shares as of that time, to be entitled to vote those Shares at the meeting. As of the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013, Walmart had 3,289,831,391 Shares outstanding. </p>

<a name="_N109CF"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">3.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What am I voting on, and what are my voting choices for each of the proposals to&nbsp;be&nbsp;voted on, at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">You are voting on the following items: </p>

<a name="_N10A72"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">4.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
Who counts the votes? Are my votes confidential?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Broadridge will count the votes. The Board has appointed two employees of Broadridge as the inspectors of election. Your proxy card or ballot and voting records will not be disclosed unless the law requires disclosure, you request disclosure, or your vote is cast in a contested election. If you write comments on your proxy card or ballot, your comments will be provided to Walmart by Broadridge, but how you voted will remain confidential. </p>

<a name="_N10A79"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">5.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What is the quorum requirement for holding the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The holders of a majority of the Shares outstanding as of the record date for the meeting must be present in person or represented by proxy for business to be transacted at the meeting. </p>

<a name="_N10A80"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">6.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What vote is required to elect a director at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">To be elected in an &ldquo;uncontested election&rdquo; of directors, which under our Bylaws is an election in which the number of nominees for director is not greater than the number of directors to be elected, a director nominee must receive affirmative votes representing a majority of the votes cast by the holders of Shares present in person or represented by proxy at the meeting and entitled to vote on the election of directors (a &ldquo;majority vote&rdquo;). To be elected in a &ldquo;contested election&rdquo; of directors, which our Bylaws define as an election in which the number of nominees for director is greater than the number of directors to be elected, a director nominee must receive a plurality of the votes of the holders of Shares present in person or represented by proxy at the meeting and entitled to vote on the election of directors. We expect the election of directors at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting to be an uncontested election. </p>

<a name="_N10A87"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">7.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What happens if a director nominee fails to receive a majority vote in an uncontested election at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Any incumbent director who is a director nominee and who does not receive a majority vote must promptly tender his or her offer of resignation as a director for consideration by the Board. Each director standing for reelection at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting has agreed to resign, effective upon acceptance of such resignation by the Board, if he or she does not receive a majority vote. The Board must accept or reject such resignation within 90 days following certification of the shareholder vote in accordance with the procedures established by the Bylaws. If a director&rsquo;s resignation offer is not accepted by the Board, that director will continue to serve until our company&rsquo;s next annual shareholders&rsquo; meeting and his or her successor is duly elected and qualified or until the director&rsquo;s earlier death, resignation, or removal. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Any director nominee who is not an incumbent director and who fails to receive a majority vote in an uncontested election will not be elected as a director, and a vacancy will be left on the Board. The Board, in its sole discretion, may either fill a vacancy resulting from a director nominee not receiving a majority vote pursuant to the Bylaws or decrease the size of the Board to eliminate the vacancy. </p>

<a name="_N10A90"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">8.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What vote is required to pass the other proposals at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the Shares present in person or represented by proxy at the meeting and entitled to vote on the proposal at issue is required for: (i)&nbsp;the ratification of the appointment of E&amp;Y as Walmart&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal 2014; (ii)&nbsp;the adoption of a non-binding advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; (iii)&nbsp;the approval of the Management Incentive Plan, as amended; and (iv) the adoption of each of the shareholder proposals. </p>

<a name="_N10A97"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">9.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What is the effect of an &ldquo;abstain&rdquo; vote or a &ldquo;broker non-vote&rdquo; on the proposals to&nbsp;be&nbsp;voted on at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Abstentions.</i>
</b> A Share voted &ldquo;abstain&rdquo; with respect to any proposal is considered as present and entitled to vote with respect to that proposal, but is not considered a vote cast with respect to that proposal. Therefore, an abstention will not have any effect on the election of directors. Because each of the other proposals requires the affirmative vote of the holders of a majority of the Shares present and entitled to vote on each such proposal in order to pass, an abstention will have the effect of a vote against each of the other proposals. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Broker Non-Votes.</i>
</b> A &ldquo;broker non-vote&rdquo; occurs if your Shares are not registered in your name (that is, you hold your Shares in &ldquo;street name&rdquo;) and you do not provide the record holder of your Shares (usually a bank, broker, or other nominee) with voting instructions on any matter as to which, under the NYSE Listed Company Rules, a broker may not vote without instructions from you, but the broker nevertheless provides a proxy for your Shares. Shares as to which a broker non-vote occurs are considered present for purposes of determining whether a quorum exists, but are not considered &ldquo;votes cast&rdquo; or Shares &ldquo;entitled to vote&rdquo; with respect to a voting matter. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;11</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Under the NYSE Listed Company Rules: (i) the election of directors; (ii) the non-binding advisory vote to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; (iii)&nbsp;the approval of the Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Management Incentive Plan, as amended; and (iv) each of the shareholder proposals described in this proxy statement are not matters on which a broker may vote without your instructions. Therefore, if your Shares are not registered in your name and you do not provide instructions to the record holder of your Shares regarding these proposals, a broker non-vote as to your Shares will result with respect to these proposals. The ratification of the appointment of independent accountants is a routine item under the NYSE Listed Company Rules. As a result, brokers who do not receive instructions from you as to how to vote on that matter generally may vote on that matter in their discretion. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">If your Shares are held of record by a bank, broker, or other nominee, we urge you to give instructions to your bank, broker, or other nominee as to how you wish your Shares to be voted so you may participate in the shareholder voting on these important matters. </p>

<a name="_N10AAB"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">10.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
How do I vote?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The process for voting your Shares depends on how your Shares are held. Generally, you may hold Shares as a &ldquo;record holder&rdquo; (that is, in your own name) or in &ldquo;street name&rdquo; (that is, through a nominee, such as a broker or bank). If you hold Shares in &ldquo;street name,&rdquo; you are considered to be the &ldquo;beneficial owner&rdquo; of those Shares. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Voting for Record Holders.</i>
</b> If you are a record holder, you may vote by proxy or you may vote in person at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. If you are a record holder and would like to vote your Shares by proxy prior to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, you have three ways to vote: </p>



<table style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" align="center" width="100%" cellpadding="2" frame="void">

<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="77.44251968503947" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:top;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">call 1-800-690-6903 using a touch-tone phone  (toll charges may apply for calls made from outside the United&nbsp;States) and follow the instructions provided on the call;</p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="77.44251968503947" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">

</td>
</tr>
