<img src="graphic_mail.jpg">
</p></td>

<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="414.3968503937005" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt; color: #000000" align="left">if you received a proxy card in the mail,  complete, sign, date, and mail the proxy card in the return envelope provided to you.</p>

</td>
</tr>
</table>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Please note that telephone and internet voting will close at 11:59&nbsp;p.m. Eastern time on June&nbsp;6,&nbsp;2013. If you wish to vote by telephone or internet, follow the instructions on your proxy card (if you received a paper copy of the proxy materials) or in the notice of availability of the proxy materials. If you received a proxy card in the mail and wish to vote by completing and returning the proxy card via mail, please note that your completed proxy card must be received by no later than the time the polls close for voting at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">If you plan to attend the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting and wish to vote in person, you will be given, upon your request, a ballot at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. Even if you vote by proxy prior to June&nbsp;7,&nbsp;2013, you may still attend the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Voting for Holders in &ldquo;Street Name.&rdquo;</i>
</b> If your Shares are held in the name of a broker, bank, or other nominee (that is, you hold your Shares in &ldquo;street name&rdquo;), you should receive separate instructions from the holder of your Shares describing how to vote. Nonetheless, if your Shares are held in the name of a broker, bank, or other nominee and you want to vote in person, you will need to obtain (and bring with you to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting) a legal proxy from the record holder of your Shares (who must have been the record holder of your Shares as of the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013) indicating that you were a beneficial owner of Shares as of the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013, as well as the number of Shares of which you were the beneficial owner on the record date, and appointing you as the record holder&rsquo;s proxy to vote the Shares covered by that proxy at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Voting of Shares Held in the 401(k) Plan or the Wal-Mart Puerto Rico 401(k) Plan.</i>
</b> If your Shares are held through the 401(k) Plan or the Wal-Mart Puerto Rico 401(k) Plan, you must provide instructions on how you wish to vote your Shares held through such plans no later than 11:59&nbsp;p.m. Eastern time on June&nbsp;4,&nbsp;2013. If you do not provide such instructions by that time, your Shares will be voted by the Retirement Plans Committee of the respective plan&nbsp;in accordance with the rules of the applicable plan. </p>

<a name="_N10B02"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">11.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What if I do not specify a choice for a proposal when returning a proxy?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Unless you indicate otherwise, the persons named as proxies on the proxy card will vote your Shares: FOR the election of each of the nominees for director named in this proxy statement; FOR the ratification of E&amp;Y as Walmart&rsquo;s independent accountants for fiscal 2014; FOR the non-binding advisory resolution to approve the compensation of the company&rsquo;s NEOs; FOR the approval of the Management Incentive Plan, as amended; and AGAINST each of the shareholder proposals appearing in this proxy statement. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;12</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<a name="_N10B0C"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">12.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
I completed and returned my proxy card, but I have changed my mind about how I&nbsp;want to vote. Can I revoke my proxy?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Yes, if you are a record holder, you may revoke a previously submitted proxy by: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">delivering a written notice of revocation to Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate Secretary at the address provided in the Notice of 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting included in this proxy statement before the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">signing a proxy bearing a later date than the proxy being revoked and delivering it to Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate Secretary at the address provided in the Notice of 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting included in this proxy statement before the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting; or </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">voting in person at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">If your Shares are held in street name through a broker, bank, or other nominee, you should contact the record holder of your Shares regarding how to revoke your voting instructions. </p>

<a name="_N10B1B"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">13.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
Why did I receive a notice regarding the internet availability of the proxy materials instead of a paper copy of the proxy materials?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Important Notice Regarding the Availability of Proxy Materials for the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</i>
</b> This year, we are again taking advantage of the rules of the SEC that allow us to furnish our proxy materials over the internet. As a result, we are mailing a notice of availability of the proxy materials on the internet, rather than a full paper set of the proxy materials, to many of our shareholders. This notice of availability includes instructions on how to access our proxy materials on the internet, as well as instructions on how shareholders may obtain a paper copy of the proxy materials by mail or a printable copy electronically. Shareholders who have affirmatively requested electronic delivery of our proxy materials will receive instructions via e-mail regarding how to access these materials electronically. All other shareholders, including shareholders who have previously requested to receive a paper copy of the materials, will receive a full paper set of the proxy materials by mail. This distribution process will contribute to our sustainability efforts and will reduce the costs of printing and distributing our proxy materials. </p>

<a name="_N10B24"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">14.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
How can I access the proxy materials over the internet? How can I request a paper copy of the proxy materials?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Accessing the Proxy Materials over the Internet.</i>
</b> You can access the proxy statement and the Annual Report to Shareholders in the &ldquo;Investors&rdquo; section of Walmart&rsquo;s corporate website at <i>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports. </i>In accordance with the rules of the SEC, we do not use software that identifies visitors accessing our proxy materials on our website. If you wish to join in Walmart&rsquo;s sustainability efforts, you can instruct Walmart to deliver its proxy materials for future annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings to you electronically by e-mail. If you choose to access future proxy materials electronically, you will receive an e-mail with instructions containing a link to the website where those materials are available and a link to the proxy voting website. Your election to access proxy materials electronically will remain in effect until you terminate it. You may choose this method of delivery in the &ldquo;Investors&rdquo; section of Walmart&rsquo;s corporate website at <i>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports.</i>

</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Obtaining a Paper Copy of the Proxy Materials.</i>
</b> If you received a notice regarding the internet availability of the proxy materials, you will find instructions about how to obtain a paper copy of the proxy materials and the Annual Report to Shareholders in your notice. If you received an e-mail notification as to the availability of the proxy materials, you will find instructions about how to obtain a paper copy of the proxy materials and the Annual Report to Shareholders as part of that e-mail notification. We will mail a paper copy of the proxy materials and the Annual Report to Shareholders to all shareholders to whom we do not send a notice of availability or an e-mail notification regarding the internet availability of the proxy materials. </p>

<a name="_N10B36"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">15.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
What should I do if I receive more than one notice or e-mail notification about the internet availability of the proxy materials or more than one paper copy of the proxy materials?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Some shareholders may receive more than one notice of internet availability, more than one e-mail notification, or more than one paper copy of the proxy materials, including multiple proxy cards. For example, if you hold your Shares in more than one brokerage account, you may receive a separate notice of availability, a separate e-mail notification, or a separate voting instruction form for each brokerage account in which you hold Shares. If you are a shareholder of record and your Shares are registered in more than one name, you may receive a separate notice of availability, a separate e-mail notification, or a separate set of paper proxy materials and proxy card for each name in which you hold Shares. To vote all of your Shares, you must complete, sign, date, and return each proxy card you receive or vote the Shares to which each proxy card relates by telephone, internet, or mobile device as described above, or vote in person as described above. If you have Shares held in one or more &ldquo;street names,&rdquo; you must complete, sign, date, and return to each bank, broker, or other nominee through which you hold Shares each voting instruction form received from that bank, broker, or other nominee (or obtain a proxy from each such nominee holder if you wish to vote in person at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting). </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;13</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<a name="_N10B40"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">16.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
How can I attend the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting? What do I need to bring?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>Only shareholders who own Shares as of the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013 are entitled to attend the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting.</i>
</b> You will be admitted to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting only if you present valid proof of Share ownership as described below and photo identification (such as a valid driver&rsquo;s license or passport) at an entrance to Bud Walton Arena, the facility at which the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting is held. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">If your Shares are registered in your name and you received your proxy materials by mail, you should bring the proxy statement you received in the mail or the proxy card that you received in the mail (or, if you have already completed and returned your proxy card, the top part of the proxy card marked &ldquo;keep this portion for your records&rdquo;) to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">If your Shares are registered in your name and you received a notice of internet availability of the proxy materials in the mail, you should bring that notice of internet availability with you to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">If you received an e-mail with instructions containing a link to the website where our proxy materials are available and a link to the proxy voting website, bring that e-mail with you to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">If you are a beneficial owner of Shares and your Shares are held in street name as described above, you will be admitted to the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting only if you present either a valid legal proxy from your bank, broker, or other nominee as to your Shares, the notice of internet availability of the proxy materials (if you received one), a voting instruction form that you received from your bank, broker, or other nominee (if you have not already completed and returned the voting instruction form), or a recent bank, brokerage, or other statement showing that you owned Shares as of the close of business on April&nbsp;11,&nbsp;2013. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>
<i>The use of cameras, camcorders, videotaping equipment, and other recording devices will not be permitted in Bud Walton Arena.  Attendees may not bring into the arena large packages or other material that could pose a safety or disruption hazard (e.g. fireworks, noisemakers, horns, confetti, etc.).</i>
</b> Photographs and videos taken at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting may be used by Walmart. By attending the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, you will be agreeing to Walmart&rsquo;s use of those photographs and waive any claim or rights with respect to those photographs and videos and their use. </p>

<a name="_N10B55"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">17.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
I am unable to attend the meeting in person. Can I view the meeting via webcast?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Yes. If you are unable to attend the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting in person, we invite you to view a live webcast of the meeting at <i>http://stock.walmart.com/annual-reports</i>. The webcast of the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting will be available for viewing on our corporate website for a limited time after the meeting. </p>

<a name="_N10B5F"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">18.</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;
When will the company announce the voting results?
</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">We will announce the preliminary voting results at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. We will report the final results in a press release on or before June 10, 2013, which will be available on our corporate website, and in a Current Report on Form&nbsp;8-K filed with the SEC on or before June 13, 2013. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>

<a name="_N10B69"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:30pt;padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:27pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">

INFORMATION ABOUT THE BOARD

</font>
</p>

<a name="_N10B6C"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">What is the nomination process for director candidates?</font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Pursuant to Walmart&rsquo;s charter and Corporate Governance Guidelines, both of which are available to shareholders on our corporate website at <i>http://&zwnj;stock.&zwnj;walmart.com/corporate-governance/governance-documents</i>, the&nbsp;CNGC is responsible for identifying, evaluating, and recommending potential candidates to the Board for nomination for election to the Board. The CNGC&rsquo;s process for identifying potential candidates for nomination to the Board is an ongoing one. Throughout the year, the CNGC actively engages in director succession planning and regularly evaluates whether the addition of a director or directors with particular attributes, experience, or a particular skill set, would contribute to enhancing the Board&rsquo;s effectiveness, achieving the company&rsquo;s business objectives, and serving our company&rsquo;s and shareholders&rsquo; long-term best interests. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">As a part of the candidate search process, the CNGC may consult with other directors and senior officers and may hire a search firm to assist in identifying and evaluating potential candidates. SpencerStuart currently serves as our company&rsquo;s director candidate search consultant. In this capacity, SpencerStuart seeks out candidates who have the experience, skills, and characteristics that the CNGC has identified for potential candidates, conducts an extensive search for, and analysis of, potential candidates, and then presents the most qualified candidates to the CNGC and our Chairman. If the CNGC decides, on the basis of its preliminary review, to proceed with further consideration of a potential candidate, the chair of the CNGC and other members of the CNGC, as well as other members of the Board, as appropriate, may interview the candidate. The CNGC then either makes its recommendation to the Board to fill a vacancy or add an additional member or recommends to the Board a slate of candidates for nomination for election to the Board.  Timothy P. Flynn, who was appointed to the Board on July 27, 2012, was initially identified as a potential candidate for the Board by SpencerStuart, and his appointment to the Board and nomination for election at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting was a result of the process outlined above. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">S. Robson Walton and Jim C. Walton are members of a group that beneficially owns more than five&nbsp;percent of the outstanding Shares. Any participation by them in the nomination process is considered to be in their capacities as members of the Board and is not considered to be recommendations from security holders who beneficially own more than five&nbsp;percent of the outstanding Shares. </p>

<a name="_N10B79"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">Can shareholders recommend director candidates?</font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Yes. Shareholders may recommend candidates for consideration by the Board by writing to: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="center">Wal-Mart Stores,&nbsp;Inc. Board of Directors </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="center">c/o Gordon Y. Allison, Vice President and General Counsel, Corporate Division </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="center">702 Southwest 8<sup>th</sup> Street </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="center">Bentonville, Arkansas 72716-0215 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The recommendation must include the following information: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">the candidate&rsquo;s name and business address; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">a resume or curriculum vitae that demonstrates the candidate&rsquo;s qualifications to serve as a director as described on page 16 and in our Corporate Governance Guidelines; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">a statement as to whether or not, during the past ten years, the candidate has been convicted in a criminal proceeding (other than for minor traffic violations), has been involved in any other legal proceeding or has been the subject of, or a party to, any order, judgment, decree, finding or sanction (including any order, judgment, decree, finding or sanction issued by an entity such as a stock or commodities exchange) relating to an alleged violation of laws or regulations relating to securities, commodities, financial institutions, insurance companies, mail or wire fraud, or fraud in connection with a business entity, in each case giving the date and a brief description of the conviction, order, judgment, decree, finding, or sanction, the name of the proceeding, and the disposition; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">a statement from the candidate that he or she consents to serve on the Board if elected; and </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">a statement from the person submitting the candidate that he or she is the registered holder of Shares, or, if the shareholder is not the registered holder, a written statement from the record holder of the Shares (usually a broker or bank) verifying that at the time the shareholder submitted the candidate that he or she was a beneficial owner of Shares. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">All candidates recommended for nomination to the Board by a shareholder pursuant to the requirements above will be submitted to the CNGC for its review. Any candidates recommended by shareholders in accordance with the above requirements will be evaluated by the CNGC on the same basis as all other director candidates. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">See &ldquo;Submission of Shareholder Proposals&rdquo; on page 35 for information regarding how shareholders may bring business before Walmart&rsquo;s annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings, either through the shareholder proposal process or pursuant to the advance notice provision of Walmart&rsquo;s Bylaws. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;15</p>

<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<a name="_N10B9D"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:30pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold">
<font color="#007DC3">Proposal No.&nbsp;1</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;Election of Directors </p>

<a name="_N10BA2"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">What am I voting on? </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">You are voting on a proposal to elect the nominees named below as directors of the company. Your proxy holder will vote your Shares for the election of each of the Board&rsquo;s nominees named below unless you instruct otherwise. </p>

<a name="_N10BA6"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">How often are directors elected and how many nominees are up for election? </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Walmart&rsquo;s directors are elected at each annual shareholders&rsquo; meeting and hold office until the next annual meeting and until their successors are duly elected and qualified or until their earlier resignation, death, or removal. Each of the director nominees currently serves on the Board and was elected by the shareholders at the 2012 Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, with the exception of Timothy P. Flynn, who was appointed to the Board in July&nbsp;2012. James W. Breyer, M. Michele Burns, and Arne M. Sorenson, who are currently directors of the company, will not stand for reelection at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">If the shareholders elect all of the director nominees named in this proxy statement at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, Walmart will have 14&nbsp;directors. The Board has authority under the Bylaws to fill vacancies and to increase or, upon the occurrence of a vacancy, decrease the Board&rsquo;s size between annual shareholders&rsquo; meetings. The Board has established the size of the Board immediately after the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting to be 14 directors. </p>

<a name="_N10BAC"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">What if a nominee is unwilling or unable to serve as a director? </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Each director nominee has previously consented to serve on the Board if elected. If a nominee is unable to serve as a director, your proxy holder may vote for any substitute candidate nominated by the Board. </p>

<a name="_N10BB0"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">What qualifications does the Compensation, Nominating and Governance Committee consider when selecting candidates? </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">In fulfilling its responsibility for identifying and evaluating director candidates, in accordance with Walmart&rsquo;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the CNGC selects potential candidates on the basis of: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">outstanding achievement in their professional careers; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">broad experience and wisdom; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">personal and professional integrity; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">ability to make independent, analytical inquiries; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">experience with and understanding of the business environment; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">willingness and ability to devote adequate time to Board duties; and </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">such other experience, attributes, and skills that the CNGC may determine as&nbsp;qualifying candidates for service on the Board. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Depending on the current composition of the Board and Board committees and the company&rsquo;s current needs and business priorities, the CNGC may also seek director candidates who possess certain experience, skills, or or other attributes, including in the following areas: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">leadership; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">technology and e-commerce; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">global or international business; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">finance, accounting, or financial reporting; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">retail; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">legal; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">marketing or brand management; and </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">public relations or advertising. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The CNGC also considers whether a potential candidate satisfies the independence and other requirements for service on the Board, as set forth in the NYSE Listed Company Rules, the SEC&rsquo;s rules, and other applicable laws, rules, or regulations. Additional information regarding director qualifications and the nomination process for director candidates is set forth in the CNGC&rsquo;s charter and our Corporate Governance Guidelines. </p>

<a name="_N10BD6"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Does the Board consider diversity in the nomination process? </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Yes. As provided in our company&rsquo;s Corporate Governance Guidelines, the Board is committed to diversified membership. The Board will not discriminate on the basis of race, color, national origin, gender, sexual orientation, religion, or disability in selecting nominees. Diversity and inclusion are values embedded into Walmart&rsquo;s culture and fundamental to its business. In keeping with those values, when assessing a candidate, the CNGC and the Board consider the different viewpoints and experiences that a candidate could bring to the Board and how those viewpoints and experiences could enhance the Board&rsquo;s effectiveness in the execution of its responsibilities. In addition, the Board assesses the diversity of the Board and Board committees as a part of its annual self-evaluation process. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;16</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<a name="_N10BDD"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Who are the 2013 director nominees? </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The following candidates for election as directors at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting have been nominated by the Board based on the recommendation of the CNGC. The information set forth below includes, with respect to each nominee, his or her age, principal occupation and employment during the past five years, the year in which he or she first became a director of Walmart, and directorships of other public companies held by each nominee during the past five years. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">In addition to the information presented below regarding each nominee&rsquo;s specific experience, qualifications, attributes, and skills that led the Board to conclude that he or she should serve as a director, our Board believes that each of our director nominees has demonstrated the qualifications described above under &ldquo;What qualifications does the Compensation, Nominating and Governance Committee consider when selecting candidates?". </p>

<p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-weight:bold; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">
<font color="#007DC3">The Board recommends that shareholders vote FOR each of the nominees named below for election to the Board. </font>
</p>

<font color="#007DC3">Aida M. Alvarez</font>

</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236218" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Joined the Board:</b> 2006 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Age:</b> 63 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Board Committee:</b> Audit </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships: </b>UnionBanCal Corporation</p>

<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez is the former Administrator of the U.S. Small Business Administration and was a member of President Clinton&rsquo;s Cabinet from 1997 to 2001.&nbsp;She was the founding Director of the Office of Federal Housing Enterprise Oversight (the &ldquo;OFHEO&rdquo;) from 1993 to 1997. Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez was a vice president in public finance at First Boston Corporation and Bear Stearns&nbsp;&amp; Co.,&nbsp;Inc. prior to 1993.&nbsp;She previously served as the Chair of the Latino Community Foundation of San Francisco and has served as a director of UnionBanCal Corporation and Union Bank, N.A. since 2004, and of Progress Financial Corporation since 2011. Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez has been a member of the Board since 2006. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include her expertise in government and executive experience that she gained through her years in President Clinton&rsquo;s Cabinet and from her executive role at government agencies. As founding Director of the OFHEO, Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez was responsible for leading the agency with financial oversight responsibility for the secondary mortgage market and ensuring the capital adequacy and financial safety and soundness of two government-sponsored enterprises&nbsp;&ndash; the Federal National Mortgage Association and the Federal Home Loan Mortgage Corporation. Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez brings to the Board extensive knowledge of the federal government and insight into public policy, as well as leadership experience gained through her directorship of the OFHEO, oversight of the U.S. Small Business Administration and service on boards of directors, including her service on the Board and the Audit Committee. The&nbsp;Board also benefits from Ms.&nbsp;Alvarez&rsquo;s knowledge of investment banking and finance as a result of her experience as an investment banker.</p>

<font color="#007DC3">James I. Cash, Jr.</font>

</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<img src="picture_jicashjr.jpg">
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236224" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Joined the Board:</b> 2006</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Age:</b> 65</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Board Committees:</b> Audit Commitee; TeCC</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships:</b> The Chubb Corporation; General Electric Company</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Dr. Cash is the James&nbsp;E. Robison Emeritus Professor of Business Administration at Harvard Business School, where he served from July&nbsp;1976 to October&nbsp;2003. Dr.&nbsp;Cash served as the Senior Associate Dean and Chairman of HBS Publishing while on the faculty of the Harvard Business School, and also served as Chairman of the MBA Program. While on the faculty of Harvard Business School, Dr. Cash&rsquo;s research focused on the strategic use of information technology in the service sector, and specifically the development of a performance measurement system for large information technology organizations. Dr. Cash holds an advanced degree in accounting and has been published extensively in accounting and information technology journals. He currently provides management development and consulting services through The Cash Catalyst, LLC, which Dr. Cash formed in 2009. He has served as a director of The Chubb Corporation since 1996 and of General Electric Company since 1997. Dr. Cash has served as a director of a number of other public companies, including Phase Forward Incorporated from October&nbsp;2003 to May&nbsp;2009, and Microsoft Corporation from May&nbsp;2001 to November&nbsp;2009, and has served on the audit committees of several public companies. He also serves as a director for several private companies. Dr. Cash has been a member of the Board since 2006. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Dr. Cash&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include his knowledge of management and information technology gained through his years of research, publishing, and teaching on the subject, as well as through his service on the boards of directors of technology companies and his consulting activities. In addition, Dr.&nbsp;Cash provides the Board with financial, accounting, and strategic planning expertise gained through his education, his career in academia, and his service on the boards of directors and audit committees of large multinational public companies in a variety of industries.</p>

</td>
</tr>

<font><i>

<font color="#007DC3">Roger C. Corbett</font>

</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<img src="picture_rccorbett.jpg">
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236224" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Joined the Board:</b> 2006</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Age:</b> 70</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Board Committee:</b> SPFC</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships:</b> Fairfax Media Limited; Mayne Pharma Group Limited; PrimeAg Australia Limited
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Corbett is the retired CEO and Group Managing Director of Woolworths Limited (&ldquo;Woolworths&rdquo;), the largest retail company in Australia, where he served from 1990 to 2006. He is a director of The Reserve Bank of Australia and Chairman of PrimeAg Australia Limited (a major Australian farming enterprise). He is the Chairman of Fairfax Media Limited (a major Australian newspaper, magazine, and internet publisher), where he also serves as Chairman of that company&rsquo;s Nominations Committee and formerly served as Chairman of that company&rsquo;s Audit and Risk Committee. He also is a director and non-executive Chairman of Mayne Pharma Group Limited, an Australian specialty pharmaceutical company (which recently purchased Metrics, Inc., a pharmaceutical company in North Carolina), and a former member of the Prime Minister&rsquo;s Community Business Partnership. Mr.&nbsp;Corbett is a Member of the Australian Indigenous Chamber of Commerce Advisory Board and a former founding director of Outback Stores, a commercial venture supported by the government to provide retail facilities for communities in remote Australia. He is a member of the Advisory Council of the Australian Graduate School of Management for the University of New South Wales, and is also the former Chairman of CIES Food Business Forum (France). Mr.&nbsp;Corbett is also Chairman of the Salvation Army Advisory Board, is the former Chairman of the Sydney Children&rsquo;s Hospitals Network (Randwick&nbsp;&amp; Westmead) Advisory Board, is a member of the Dean&rsquo;s Advisory Group of the Faculty of Medicine at the University of Sydney, and a member of the University of New South Wales Centre for Healthy Brain Ageing Advisory Board. Mr.&nbsp;Corbett has been a member of the Board since 2006. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Corbett&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include his extensive knowledge of the retail industry and his understanding of financial, operational, and strategic issues facing large retail companies gained through his experience as a CEO of a major retail company and his more than 40 years of leadership experience in the retail industry. Mr.&nbsp;Corbett also contributes his demonstrated leadership and strategic planning experience gained as the CEO of a publicly traded retailer and through his service on the boards of directors of various for-profit and non-profit organizations, including his service on the Board and the SPFC. In addition, Mr.&nbsp;Corbett brings to the Board an international perspective and understanding of international markets.</p>

</td>
</tr>

<font color="#007DC3">Douglas N. Daft</font>

</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:18pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt;" align="center">

<img src="picture_dndaft.jpg">
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236224" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Joined the Board:</b> 2005</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Age:</b> 70</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Board Committee:</b> CNGC</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships:</b> None</p>
</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Daft is the retired Chairman and CEO of The Coca-Cola Company, a beverage manufacturer, where he served in that capacity from February&nbsp;2000 until May&nbsp;2004 and in various other capacities, including responsibility for various international markets, since 1969. Mr.&nbsp;Daft served as a director of The McGraw-Hill Companies,&nbsp;Inc. from 2003 to April&nbsp;2012, Green Mountain Coffee Roasters,&nbsp;Inc. from December&nbsp;2009 to May&nbsp;2012, and Sistema-Hals from September&nbsp;2006 until December&nbsp;2009. Among additional endeavors, Mr.&nbsp;Daft is a member of the European Advisory Council for N.M. Rothschild&nbsp;&amp; Sons Limited and a member of the advisory boards of Longreach,&nbsp;Inc., Tisbury Capital, and Thomas&nbsp;H. Lee Partners. Mr.&nbsp;Daft has been a member of the Board since 2005. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Daft&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include his international business leadership experience gained through his service as Chairman and CEO of a major global public company. Through his service at The Coca-Cola Company, Mr.&nbsp;Daft brings to the Board extensive expertise in brand management, marketing, finance, strategic planning, and overseeing the operations of a global corporation. In addition, through his years of service on the boards of several large companies in a variety of industries, including his service on the Board and the CNGC, Mr.&nbsp;Daft provides diverse and valuable corporate governance, finance, operational, and strategic expertise to the Board.</p>

</td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Age:</b> 63</p>
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">
<b>Board Committees: </b> Executive Committee; Global Compensation Committee</p>

<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">
<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Duke is the President and CEO of Walmart and has served in that position since February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2009. Prior to this appointment, he held other positions with Walmart since joining our company in July&nbsp;1995, including Vice Chairman with responsibility for Walmart International beginning in September&nbsp;2005 and Executive Vice President and President and CEO of Walmart U.S. beginning in April&nbsp;2003. Mr.&nbsp;Duke serves on the board of directors of The Consumer Goods Forum, the executive committee of the Business Roundtable, and the executive board of Conservation International&rsquo;s Center for Environmental Leadership in Business. He also serves on the board of advisors for the University of Arkansas and the advisory board of the Tsinghua University School of Economics and Management in Beijing, China. Mr.&nbsp;Duke has been a member of the Board since November&nbsp;2008. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Duke&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include his decades of experience in the retail industry, his years of executive leadership experience across multiple operating divisions of our company, his knowledge of international markets and international retailing gained through his oversight of our International division, and his expertise in corporate strategy, development, and execution.</p>

</td>

<tr>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Flynn is the retired Chairman of KPMG International (&ldquo;KPMG&rdquo;), a professional services firm, where he served in that capacity from 2007 to October&nbsp;2011. He&nbsp;previously served as Chairman from 2005 to 2010 and Chief Executive Officer from 2005 to 2008 of KPMG LLP in the U.S., the largest member firm of KPMG International. Mr.&nbsp;Flynn serves as a member of the board of directors of JPMorgan Chase&nbsp;&amp; Co. and as a member of the board of trustees of the University of St. Thomas, St. Paul, Minnesota. He has previously served as trustee of the Financial Accounting Standards Board, a member of the World Economic Forum&rsquo;s International Business Council, and was a founding member of The Prince of Wales&rsquo; International Integrated Reporting Committee. Mr.&nbsp;Flynn has been a member of the Board since 2012. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

Through his experience at KPMG, Mr.&nbsp;Flynn brings to the Board extensive experience in global business leadership, accounting, auditing, risk management, and regulatory affairs.</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Joined the Board:</b> 2012 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Age: </b>37 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Board Committees:</b> SPFC; TeCC </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships: </b>Yahoo! Inc.</p>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Ms.&nbsp;Mayer is President and Chief Executive Officer and a member of the board of directors of Yahoo!&nbsp;Inc. (&ldquo;Yahoo!&rdquo;), a digital media company, positions she has held since July&nbsp;2012. Prior to assuming her role at Yahoo!, Ms.&nbsp;Mayer was the Vice President of Local and Maps for Google Inc. (&ldquo;Google&rdquo;) beginning in 2010, where she led the product management and engineering efforts of Google&rsquo;s local, mobile, and location-based products, including Google Maps, Google Maps for Mobile, Local Search, Google Earth, and Street View. Ms.&nbsp;Mayer served in a variety of other capacities after joining Google as its first female engineer in 1999, and was responsible for launching hundreds of products and features during that time. Concurrently with her work at Google, Ms.&nbsp;Mayer taught introductory computer programming classes at Stanford University. Ms.&nbsp;Mayer holds a bachelor&rsquo;s degree in symbolic systems and a master&rsquo;s degree in computer science from Stanford University. Ms.&nbsp;Mayer serves on the boards of the San Francisco Museum of Modern Art, the San Francisco Ballet, and the New&nbsp;York City Ballet. Ms.&nbsp;Mayer has served on the Board since 2012. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Ms.&nbsp;Mayer&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include her extensive expertise and insight into the technology and consumer internet industries. Through her experience at Yahoo! and Google, Ms.&nbsp;Mayer brings to the Board long-term experience in internet product development, engineering, and brand management. In addition, the Board benefits from Ms.&nbsp;Mayer&rsquo;s expertise in governance and strategic planning gained through her experience in her positions at Yahoo! and the boards of numerous non-profit organizations.</p>


</td>
</tr>

<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236224" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">

<b>Joined the Board: </b>2008 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Age:</b> 43 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Board Committees:</b> TeCC; Global Compensation Committee </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships:</b> Baidu,&nbsp;Inc.; Hyatt Hotels Corporation</p>

</td>

<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Penner has been a General Partner of Madrone Capital Partners (&ldquo;Madrone&rdquo;), an investment management firm, since 2005. From 2002 to 2005, he served as Walmart&rsquo;s Senior Vice President and CFO - Japan. Before serving in that role, Mr.&nbsp;Penner held the position of Senior Vice President of Finance and Strategy for Walmart.com. Prior to working for Walmart, Mr.&nbsp;Penner was a General Partner at Peninsula Capital, an early stage venture capital fund, and a financial analyst for Goldman, Sachs&nbsp;&amp; Co. Mr.&nbsp;Penner has been a member of the board of directors of Baidu,&nbsp;Inc. since 2004 and of Hyatt Hotels Corporation since 2007. He also serves on the boards of directors of eHarmony,&nbsp;Inc. and Castleton Commodities International, LLC. Mr.&nbsp;Penner has been a member of the Board since 2008. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Penner&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include his knowledge of international business, particularly in Asia, gained through his former service as CFO of Walmart&rsquo;s operations in Japan and his service on the boards of directors of Baidu,&nbsp;Inc. and 99Bill Corporation (from 2005 to 2012), both of which are based in China. Mr.&nbsp;Penner also brings technology expertise to the Board gained through his service with Walmart.com and as a director of various technology companies, including Baidu,&nbsp;Inc. and 99Bill Corporation. The Board also benefits from Mr.&nbsp;Penner&rsquo;s expertise in strategic planning, finance, and investment matters gained through his leadership of Madrone, his business leadership experience, and his service on the boards of directors of public and private companies in a variety of industries, including the Board.</p>

<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">
<a name="_N10D8A"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">

<font color="#007DC3">Steven S Reinemund</font>

</p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="144.85196850393686" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:bottom;" valign="">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="center">

<img src="picture_ssreinemund.jpg">
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236224" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Joined the Board:</b> 2010 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Age:</b> 65 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Board Committee:</b> CNGC </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships:</b> Exxon Mobil Corporation; American Express Company; Marriott International,&nbsp;Inc.</p>

</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="2" width="NaN" valign="centre">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund is the Dean of Business and Professor of Leadership and Strategy at Wake Forest University, positions he has held since July&nbsp;2008. Prior to joining the faculty of Wake Forest University, Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund had a distinguished 23-year career with PepsiCo,&nbsp;Inc. (&ldquo;PepsiCo&rdquo;), where he served as that company&rsquo;s Chairman of the Board from October&nbsp;2006 to May&nbsp;2007, and Chairman and CEO from May&nbsp;2001 to October&nbsp;2006. Prior to becoming Chairman and CEO, Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund was PepsiCo&rsquo;s President and Chief Operating Officer from 1999 to 2001 and Chairman and CEO of Frito-Lay&rsquo;s worldwide operations from 1996 to 1999. Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund has served as a director of Exxon Mobil Corporation, American Express Company, and Marriott International,&nbsp;Inc., all since 2007. He&nbsp;previously served as a director of Johnson&nbsp;&amp; Johnson from 2003 to 2008. Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund is also a member of the board of trustees for The Cooper Institute. Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund has been a member of the Board since 2010. </p>

<p style="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:12pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold; font-style:italic; color: #007DC3">Skills and Qualifications: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund&rsquo;s qualifications to serve on the Board include his international business leadership experience gained through his service as Chairman and CEO of a major global public company. Through his service at PepsiCo, Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund brings to the Board extensive expertise in brand management, marketing, finance, strategic planning, and overseeing the operations of a global corporation. In addition, through his service as dean of a prominent business school and on the boards of several large companies in a variety of industries, including his service on the Board and the CNGC, Mr.&nbsp;Reinemund is able to provide considerable corporate governance, finance, operational, and strategic expertise to the Board.</p>

</td>
</tr>
</table>


</i></font>
</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:9pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="left">
<i><sup>+</sup>	Gregory B. Penner is the son-in-law of S. Robson Walton.</i></p>
<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="876.5118110236224" style="padding-right:0pt;vertical-align:middle;" valign="">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Joined the Board:</b> 1999 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Age:</b> 64 </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Board Committee:</b> SPFC </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<b>Other Current Public Company Directorships:</b> None</p>
