<a name="_N15368"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">Walmart&rsquo;s Deferred Compensation Plans </font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Under the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan, which took effect on February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2012, officers may elect to defer base salary and cash incentive amounts until separation of employment from our company or until a specified payment date. Interest accrues on amounts deferred at an interest rate set annually based on the ten-year Treasury note rate on the first business day of January&nbsp;plus 2.70&nbsp;percent. The Deferred Compensation Matching Plan year ends on January&nbsp;31 of each year. For fiscal 2013, the interest rate was 4.67&nbsp;percent. In addition, our company allocates to each participant&rsquo;s Deferred Compensation Matching Plan account a matching contribution of up to six&nbsp;percent of the amount by which the participant&rsquo;s base salary and cash incentive payment exceed the then-applicable limitation in Section&nbsp;401(a)(17) of the Internal Revenue Code. A participant is required to be employed on the last day of the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan year to receive a matching contribution for that year. A participant will become vested in the matching contribution credited to his or her account once the participant has participated in the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan for three plan years after his or her initial deferral. For purposes of determining the vesting of matching contributions, participants will be given credit for their participation in the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan, which was the predecessor deferred compensation plan in effect prior to February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2012. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Deferred Compensation Matching Plan replaced the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan. Participants may no longer elect to defer amounts into the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan. However, participants&rsquo; Officer Deferred Compensation Plan account balances will continue to earn interest at the same rate as Deferred Compensation Matching Plan balances until distribution. Additionally, participants who made contributions to the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan in prior years continue to earn incentive contributions to their Officer Deferred Compensation Plan accounts, as follows: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">In the tenth year of continuous employment beginning with the year the participant first made a deferral under the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan, our company credits the deferral account with an increment equal to 20&nbsp;percent of the sum of the principal amount of base salary and cash incentive payments deferred (taking into account a maximum amount equal to 20&nbsp;percent of base salary) plus accrued interest on such amounts (the &ldquo;20&nbsp;Percent Increment&rdquo;) in each of the first six years of the participant&rsquo;s deferrals. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">In the eleventh and subsequent years of continuous employment, the 20&nbsp;Percent Increment is credited based on the recognized amount deferred five years earlier, plus earnings thereon. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">In addition, in the fifteenth year of continuous employment beginning with the year the participant first made a deferral under the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan, our company credits the deferral account with 10&nbsp;percent of the principal amount of base salary and cash incentive payments deferred (taking into account a maximum amount equal to 20&nbsp;percent of base salary) plus accrued interest on such amount (the &ldquo;10 Percent Increment&rdquo;) in each of the first six years of the participant&rsquo;s deferrals. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">In the sixteenth and subsequent years of continuous employment, the 10 Percent Increment is credited based on the amount deferred 10 years earlier, plus earnings thereon. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Only contributions to the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan are taken into account for purposes of calculating the 20 Percent Increment and 10 Percent Increment; contributions to the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan are not considered. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The SERP was designed to supplement the historic profit sharing portion of the Walmart 401(k) Plan by providing mirror contributions to participants&rsquo; accounts in excess of applicable compensation limits set by the Internal Revenue Service. Because the Walmart 401(k) Plan was amended in 2011 to eliminate the profit sharing component, the SERP was frozen to new contributions as of January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013, although a final contribution allocation with respect to participants&rsquo; cash incentive payments was made during fiscal 2013 and reported on the Fiscal 2013 Nonqualified Deferred Compensation table above. The matching contribution component of the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan is intended to replace the company contribution previously made to participants under the SERP. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;61</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Finally, officers may also elect to defer the receipt of equity awards granted under the Stock Incentive Plan until a specified payout date or until after separation from employment with Walmart. Any deferrals of vested Shares are credited with dividend equivalents until the payout date, and these dividend equivalents earn interest at the same rate as amounts deferred under the Deferred Compensation Matching Plan. For equity awards granted prior to January&nbsp;2008, officers could also elect to defer the cash equivalent of such equity awards into the Officer Deferred Compensation Plan upon vesting. </p>

<a name="_N15381"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">Potential Payments Upon Termination or Change In Control</font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Most of our company&rsquo;s plans and programs, including its deferred compensation plans, contain provisions specifying the consequences of a termination of employment. These provisions are described below. Other than the non-competition agreements described below, our company does not have any employment agreements with its NEOs. Our company does not have any pension plans or other defined benefit retirement plans in which the NEOs participate. Furthermore, our plans and programs do not have any provisions under which our NEOs would be entitled to payments, accelerated equity vestings, or other benefits upon a change in control of our company. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<i>Non-competition agreements.</i> Our company has entered into an agreement with each of our NEOs that contains, among other provisions, a covenant not to compete with our company and a covenant not to solicit our Associates for employment and that provides for certain post-termination payments to be made to such NEO. Each agreement prohibits the NEO, for a period of two years following his or her termination of employment with our company for any reason, from participating in a business that competes with our company and from soliciting our company&rsquo;s Associates for employment. For purposes of these agreements, a &ldquo;competing business&rdquo; includes any retail, wholesale, or merchandising business that sells products of the type sold by our company, is located in a country in which our company has retail operations or in which the NEO knows our company expects to have retail operations in the near future, and has annual retail sales revenue above certain thresholds. Each agreement also provides that, if Walmart terminates the NEO&rsquo;s employment for any reason other than his or her violation of Walmart policy, our company will generally pay the NEO an amount equal to two times the NEO&rsquo;s base salary, one-fourth of which is paid upon termination of employment and the balance of which is paid in bi-weekly installments over an 18-month period commencing six months after separation. In the event of a breach of the restrictive covenants contained in the agreement, the NEO would no longer have a right to receive additional payments, and the company would have a right to recoup any payments previously made. Using each NEO&rsquo;s base salary as of January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013, the maximum total payments by our company to each continuing NEO under such termination circumstances would be as follows: </p>



<table style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" align="center" width="100%" cellpadding="2" frame="void">

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">

<i>Equity awards.</i>&nbsp;Certain equity awards held by our NEOs provide for accelerated vesting in the event employment is terminated due to death or disability: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">

<i>Restricted stock.</i> Under the terms of most of our outstanding equity awards, in the event of the death of an NEO after his or her tenth year of service to our company, all unvested restricted stock held by such NEO granted during the prior three years would generally vest. In addition, certain restricted stock awards held by our NEOs provide that any Shares that would have vested within 90 days of his or her termination of employment due to death or disability would immediately vest. Upon termination of employment for any other reason, unvested restricted stock does not vest and is forfeited. The following table shows the value, as of January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013, of all unvested restricted stock that would have vested upon an NEO&rsquo;s death or disability on January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013 (based on the closing price of a Share on the NYSE on January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013, of $69.95): </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">

<i>Performance shares.</i> Certain performance shares held by our NEOs provide that in the event of the NEO&rsquo;s death after 10 years of service to our company, his or her performance shares would vest in an amount equal to the number that would have vested at the end of the applicable performance cycle. Additionally, certain performance share awards provide that if an NEO&rsquo;s employment terminates by reason of disability or by reason of death prior to completing 10 years of service to our company, a prorated portion of his or her performance shares would vest, based upon the number of full calendar months during the applicable performance cycle during which the NEO was employed. Upon termination of employment for any other reason, unvested performance shares generally do not vest and are forfeited. The following table shows the estimated value, as of January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013, of all performance shares that would have vested upon an NEO&rsquo;s death or disability on January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013 (based on the closing price of a Share on the NYSE on January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013, of $69.95 and assuming that target performance goals are achieved for each grant of performance shares): </p>



<table style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" align="center" width="100%" cellpadding="2" frame="void">
<tr>
<td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="80%" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;" valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="left">
<b>&nbsp;</b>
</p>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="10%" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;" valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>Upon Death </b>
</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>($)</b>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The CNGC has discretion to accelerate the vesting of any equity awards and to make other payments or grant other benefits upon a retirement or other severance from our company. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Our NEOs also participate in our company&rsquo;s deferred compensation plans, the general terms of which are described in the CD&amp;A and&nbsp;&ldquo;Walmart&rsquo;s Deferred Compensation Plans&rdquo; above. Upon termination of employment, the NEOs would generally be entitled to the balances in their deferred compensation accounts as disclosed in the Fiscal 2013 Nonqualified Deferred Compensation table above. The timing of each NEO&rsquo;s receipt of such deferred compensation balances would be determined by the terms of the company&rsquo;s deferred compensation plans and the deferral elections previously made by our NEOs. See &ldquo;Fiscal 2013 Nonqualified Deferred Compensation&rdquo; above for information regarding the aggregate deferred compensation totals for each NEO as of January&nbsp;31,&nbsp;2013. </p>

<a name="_N15626"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:30pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold">
<font color="#007DC3">Proposal No.&nbsp;3</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;Advisory Vote to Approve Named Executive Officer Compensation </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Section&nbsp;14A of the Exchange Act and related SEC rules require that we provide our shareholders with the opportunity to vote to approve, on a non-binding advisory basis, the compensation of our NEOs as disclosed in this proxy statement in accordance with SEC rules. We must provide this opportunity to our shareholders at least once every three years; however, following the recommendation of our shareholders at our 2011 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, our Board has chosen to hold this vote every year. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">As described above under &ldquo;Compensation Discussion and Analysis,&rdquo; our executive compensation program is designed with an emphasis on performance and is intended to closely align the interests of our NEOs with the interests of our shareholders. The CNGC regularly reviews our executive compensation program to ensure that compensation is closely tied to aspects of our company&rsquo;s performance that our executive officers can impact and that is likely to have an impact on shareholder value. Our compensation programs are also designed to balance long-term performance with shorter-term performance and to mitigate any risk that an Executive Officer would be incentivized to pursue good results with respect to a single performance measure or company division to the detriment of our company as a whole. In the Compensation Discussion and Analysis referred to above, we discuss why we believe the compensation of our NEOs for fiscal 2013 properly reflected our company&rsquo;s performance in fiscal 2013. We urge you to read carefully the Compensation Discussion and Analysis, the compensation tables, and the related narrative discussion in this proxy statement. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The vote on this proposal is advisory, which means that the vote will not be binding on Walmart, the Board, or the CNGC. The CNGC will consider the results of the vote on this proposal in connection with its regular evaluations of our executive compensation program and in establishing our NEOs&rsquo; compensation. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">In view of the foregoing, shareholders will vote on the following resolution at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting: </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">RESOLVED, that the company&rsquo;s shareholders hereby approve, on an advisory basis, the compensation of the Named Executive Officers of Walmart as disclosed in Walmart&rsquo;s Proxy Statement for the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting in accordance with the Securities and Exchange Commission&rsquo;s compensation disclosure rules. </p>

<p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-weight:bold; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">
<font color="#007DC3">The Board recommends that shareholders vote FOR this&nbsp;proposal. </font>
</p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;63</p>

</p>

<a name="_N1563A"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:30pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt; font-weight:bold">
<font color="#007DC3">Proposal No.&nbsp;4</font>&nbsp;&nbsp;Approval of the Management Incentive Plan, as Amended </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Board proposes that the shareholders approve Walmart&rsquo;s Management Incentive Plan, as that plan was recently amended (the &ldquo;Amended MIP&rdquo;). As described below, our company&rsquo;s practice is to submit the MIP for shareholder approval at least every five years in order to comply with Section 162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code. In anticipation of this submission for a shareholder vote at the 2013 Annual Shareholders&rsquo; Meeting, the Board approved certain amendments to the MIP (subject to shareholder approval of the Amended MIP) (the &ldquo;Recent Amendments&rdquo;). The Recent Amendments are intended to reflect regulatory developments and current practices in incentive plan design, and are described below. For purposes of consistency with Walmart&rsquo;s other compensatory plans, the Recent Amendments provide that the MIP and incentive plan awards thereunder will be governed by Delaware law. The MIP and incentive plan awards thereunder were previously governed by Arkansas law. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">A copy of the Amended MIP is attached to this Proxy Statement as Appendix A. The description of the Amended MIP herein is subject in its entirety to the actual terms of the Amended MIP as set forth in Appendix A to this proxy statement. We urge you to read the Amended MIP before determining how to vote on this Proposal No.&nbsp;4. The Board may amend or terminate the Amended MIP in its discretion, provided that shareholder approval is required for any amendment that, with respect to incentive plan awards under the Amended MIP made to &ldquo;covered employees&rdquo; (as defined below): (i) changes the class of Associates eligible to participate in the Amended MIP; (ii) changes the performance measures pursuant to which the performance goals under the Amended MIP are set; (iii) changes the performance goals with respect to an incentive compensation award for a particular performance period under the Amended MIP; or (iv) increases the maximum incentive award that may be paid to a participant under the Amended MIP. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Through the Amended MIP, our officers, other management Associates, and selected non-management Associates, whom, in each case, the CNGC determines have the potential to contribute significantly to the success of our company, are eligible to receive performance-based cash incentive payments on an annual basis. As of February&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2013, approximately 337,112 Associates were eligible to participate in the Amended MIP. </p>

<a name="_N15645"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Compliance with Section&nbsp;162(m) </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Amended MIP is being submitted to you for approval to comply with Section&nbsp;162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code. Section&nbsp;162(m) prohibits a company from taking a federal income tax deduction for compensation paid in excess of $1&nbsp;million during a taxable year to an Associate defined in Section&nbsp;162(m) as a &ldquo;covered employee.&rdquo;  This limit on deductibility does not apply to compensation defined in Section&nbsp;162(m) as &ldquo;qualified performance-based compensation&rdquo; so long as certain criteria are met, including shareholder approval of the plan and the performance measures under which the compensation is paid. In order to qualify as &ldquo;qualified performance-based compensation,&rdquo; shareholders must approve the performance measures available under the plan every five years. The MIP was most recently approved by shareholders at the company&rsquo;s annual shareholders&rsquo; meeting in 2008.  </p>

<a name="_N15649"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Performance Goals </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">For each incentive plan award made under the Amended MIP, the CNGC has authority to establish one or more objective performance goals, the applicable performance period, the formula for determining the amount to be paid based on achievement of the applicable performance goals, and other terms and conditions of the award. Any performance goal for any award may be based upon the performance of Walmart or the performance of any affiliate, division, or unit of Walmart or any store, groups of stores, or individual participant. Pursuant to the Recent Amendments, performance goals may also be based upon the performance of groups of individual participants in the Amended MIP. Performance goals may be absolute or may be relative to comparable measures at comparison companies or to a defined index. For awards not intended to be &ldquo;qualified performance-based compensation,&rdquo; the CNGC may establish other objective or subjective performance goals, including individual performance goals, as it deems appropriate, and such goals need not be based on one of the performance measures enumerated in the Amended MIP. The CNGC also determines the consequences with respect to an outstanding incentive plan award under the Amended MIP of the occurrence of a change in control of the company or an affiliate during the performance period or in the event that a participant, during the performance period, is hired, rehired, takes a leave of absence, transfers to a different position within Walmart or one of its affiliates, is disabled, promoted, demoted, or terminates  employment. For awards intended to be &ldquo;qualified performance-based compensation,&rdquo; these determinations must be made within the required time period, which is generally within the first 90 days of the performance period. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Recent Amendments provide that the CNGC may, for any one or more participants in connection with the grant of an award under the Amended MIP, establish a formula for determining the maximum amount payable to such participant or participants based on the level of achievement for applicable performance goals and set a methodology for determining the actual amount payable under such award (a &ldquo;plan within a plan&rdquo;), which amount may be, but need not be, based on a performance measure. Such new terms also permit the CNGC to establish an unfunded performance award pool, the aggregate amount of which will be based on achievement of a performance goal. The CNGC may specify the amount of the pool to be a&nbsp;percentage of a performance measure, a&nbsp;percentage of a performance measure in excess of a threshold amount, or another amount that need not bear a mathematical relationship to a performance measure. The maximum amount payable to a pool participant may be a stated&nbsp;percentage of the pool or of the participant&rsquo;s target award, the participant&rsquo;s compensation, or other elements, so long as the total amount allocable to all of the pool&rsquo;s participants does not exceed the aggregate amount of the pool and the participant&rsquo;s payment does not exceed the per participant award limit for covered employees discussed below. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Payment of an award under the Amended MIP may generally be made only upon achievement of the applicable performance goals if the award is to be a qualified performance-based award. The CNGC is responsible for certifying the degree to which the performance goals are met in each performance period. The CNGC has authority to adjust awards upward or downward to reflect individual performance or unanticipated factors, but only downward adjustments are </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;64</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">permitted for awards intended to be qualified performance-based awards. The CNGC may make upward or downward adjustments for an Associate who is not a covered employee on a payment date even if the Associate was potentially a covered employee on the date of the award&rsquo;s grant. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">No covered employee may receive an incentive plan award intended to qualify as performance-based compensation that is greater than $20,000,000 for a 12-month performance period or a proportionate amount for a performance period longer or shorter than 12&nbsp;months. This limit is unchanged under the Recent Amendments. </p>

<a name="_N15656"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Permitted Adjustments </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Performance goals will, to the extent applicable, be calculated based upon GAAP (or, as provided in the Recent Amendments, international financial accounting standards, as applicable). The performance goals will be adjusted to take into account the effect of the following items:  </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">changes in applicable accounting standards after the performance goal is established; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">realized investment gains and/or losses; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">extraordinary, unusual, non-recurring, or infrequent items; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">currency fluctuations; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">acquisitions or divestitures; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">litigation losses; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">financing activities; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">expenses for restructuring or productivity initiatives; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">other non-operating items; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">new laws, cases, or regulatory developments that result in unanticipated items of gain, loss, income, or expense; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">

<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">investment returns relating to investment vehicles that are unaffiliated with a company or divisional operating strategy; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">

</p>

</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">the impact on pre-tax income of interest expense attributable to the repurchase of Shares; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">extraordinary dividends or stock dividends; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">other items the CNGC determines to be required so that the operating results of the company, division, or affiliate are computed on a comparative basis from period to period. Pursuant to the Recent Amendments, such other items must be so determined by the CNGC at the time it establishes the performance goal for an incentive plan award. </p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Recent Amendments provide that the CNGC may set thresholds for adjustment items at the time it establishes performance goals such that only items that exceed certain thresholds will be adjusted. Excluded items must be objectively determinable by reference to the company&rsquo;s financial statements, notes to the company&rsquo;s financial statements, and/or management&rsquo;s discussion and analysis in the company&rsquo;s periodic reports filed with the SEC. </p>

<a name="_N1567E"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Performance Measures </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Amended MIP includes the following performance measures on which performance goals for awards intended to be &ldquo;qualified performance-based compensation&rdquo; may be based, including some performance measures added by the Recent Amendments, as indicated below: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">earnings (either in the aggregate or on a per-share basis, reflecting dilution of Shares as the CNGC deems appropriate, and, if the CNGC so determines, net of or including dividends or, as provided in the Recent Amendments, net of or including the after-tax cost of capital) before or after interest and taxes, or before or after interest, taxes, depreciation, and amortization; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, pre-tax operating earnings after interest and before incentives, service fees, and extraordinary or special items; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">earnings growth or growth in earnings per Share; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, earnings per Share from continuing operations, operating earnings, and growth in operating earnings; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">gross or net revenue and changes in annual revenues; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, revenue per Associate, revenue per full time employee, revenue per square foot or other real estate measure; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, economic value added, <i>i.e.,</i> net operating profit after tax minus the product of capital multiplied by the cost of capital; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">same store sales or comparable store sales; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, total sales levels; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">cash flow(s) (including either operating or net cash flows or, as added by the Recent Amendments, free cash flows); </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, cash flow on investment; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">total shareholder return, shareholder return based on growth measures or the attainment by the Shares of a specified value for a specified period of time, Share price, or Share price appreciation; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, net worth; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">return measures, including return ratios, return or net return on assets, net assets, equity, capital, gross sales, or, as added by the Recent Amendments, committed capital or invested capital; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">pre-tax profits, pre-tax operating margin, operating margins, operating profits, or, as added by the Recent Amendments, operating efficiency or gross profits; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">volume, market share, or market penetration with respect to specific designated products, product groups, or geographic areas, </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">operating expenses or administrative expenses; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">dividends; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">net income or net operating income; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">value of assets; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">expense or cost levels, in each case, where applicable determined on a company-wide basis or with respect to one or more specified divisions or, as added by the Recent Amendments, products; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">reduction of losses, loss ratios, or expense ratios; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">reduction in fixed costs or operating cost management; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">cost of capital, debt reduction, or, as added by the Recent Amendments, working capital targets or changes in working capital; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">productivity measures, average inventory turnover, inventory controls, and, as added by the Recent Amendments, on-shelf availability, inventory metrics, or asset quality; </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;65</p>
<hr>
<p style="page-break-before:always; margin:0pt; margin-bottom: 28pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;">
<a href="#_TOC"><font color="#0000FF">Back to Contents</font></a>
</p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">satisfaction of specified, objective business expansion goals or goals relating to acquisitions or divestitures; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as provided by the Recent Amendments, regulatory ratings; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">customer satisfaction based on specified objective goals or a company-sponsored customer survey; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">Associate diversity goals, Associate turnover, Associate attraction (which measure was added by the Recent Amendments), or specified objective social goals; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">supplier diversity goals (which measure was added by the Recent Amendments); </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">safety record; or </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">business integration. </p>

<a name="_N156C8"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Eligibility </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">To be eligible for a payment under an incentive plan award made under the Amended MIP, a participant must be employed on the last day of the performance period applicable to the award (subject to proration in the event of the participant&rsquo;s death prior to such date), must have performed the participant&rsquo;s duties to the CNGC&rsquo;s satisfaction, must have not engaged in an act deemed inimical to the company&rsquo;s best interest, and must have otherwise complied with Walmart&rsquo;s policies at all times prior to the payment of the award. In addition, pursuant to the Recent Amendments, in order to be eligible for a payment under an incentive plan award, the participant must not have breached a restrictive covenant or confidentiality requirement to which the participant was subject. </p>

<a name="_N156CC"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Clawbacks </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">If the CNGC determines, within 12&nbsp;months following the date on which an incentive plan award is paid under the Amended MIP, that (i) prior to the date of an incentive plan award&rsquo;s payment, the participant receiving the payment engaged in an act the CNGC deems inimical to the best interest of the company or violated the requirements for eligibility to receive an incentive plan award described above, or (ii) before or after the award&rsquo;s payment, the participant failed to comply with the company&rsquo;s policies, the participant must return the award payment upon the company&rsquo;s demand. In addition, the Recent Amendments provide that all awards under the Amended MIP, whether or not previously paid or deferred, will be subject to the company&rsquo;s policies or requirements and applicable law and regulations regarding clawbacks in effect from time to time. </p>

<a name="_N156D0"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Plan Benefits </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Set forth below is a table that shows incentive payments that were paid pursuant to the MIP based on performance for fiscal 2013. These are the same amounts as would have been paid pursuant to the Amended MIP inclusive of the Recent Amendments. Amounts payable for fiscal 2014 performance cannot be determined because such amounts  depend on the performance of Walmart; one or more of Walmart&rsquo;s divisions, units, affiliates, stores or groups of stores; and/or individual performance during fiscal 2014. </p>

<a name="_N1575E"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:3pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:18pt; font-weight:bold ">Importance of the Amended MIP </p>
<p style="margin-top:1pt; margin-left:8pt; margin-bottom:25pt; border-top:1pt solid #007DC3; line-height:20pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold"></p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The Board believes that the adoption of the Amended MIP is in the best interests of Walmart and its shareholders for the following reasons: </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">incentive plan awards made under the plan are instrumental in attracting and retaining key talent throughout our company; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">shareholder approval of the performance measures contained in the plan is required to maintain the tax deductibility of awards made to &ldquo;covered employees&rdquo; as defined in Section 162(m) of the Internal Revenue Code; </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">as discussed in greater detail in &ldquo;Compensation Discussion and Analysis&rdquo; beginning on page 40, incentive plan awards are a key element of our pay-for-performance philosophy with respect to our NEO compensation; and </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: -11pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">&bull;</font>
</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; padding-left: 18pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;">the Amended MIP provides for a clawback of the incentive plan award if the CNGC determines, within 12 months following the payment of an award under the plan or before the award is paid, that the participant engaged in acts deemed inimical to the best interests of the company or violated company policy, or the clawback is otherwise required by company policy.  The Recent Amendments further strengthen this clawback by providing that all incentive plan awards will be subject to the company&rsquo;s policies or requirements and applicable law and regulations regarding clawbacks in effect from time to time. </p>

<p style="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-weight:bold; font-size:12pt;" align="justify">
<font color="#007DC3">For the above reasons, the Board recommends that the shareholders vote FOR the Management Incentive Plan, as amended. </font>
</p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">
<img src="footer_walmart.jpg" style="margin-bottom:-5pt;">&nbsp;&nbsp;<i>2013 Proxy Statement</i>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;66</p>

<a name="_N1576F"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:30pt;padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:27pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:26pt;">
<font color="#007DC3">

STOCK OWNERSHIP

</font>
</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The following tables set forth ownership of Shares by major shareholders, directors, and Executive Officers of our company. There were 3,292,377,090 Shares outstanding on April&nbsp;1, 2013. </p>

<a name="_N15774"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">Holdings of Major Shareholders </font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">The following table lists the beneficial owners of five&nbsp;percent or more of the Shares outstanding as of April&nbsp;1,&nbsp;2013. </p>



<table style="margin-top:3pt; margin-bottom:12pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:10pt;" cellspacing="0" align="center" width="100%" cellpadding="2" frame="void">
<tr>
<td rowspan="2" colspan="1" width="274.87559055118106" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt;" valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="left">
<b>Name&nbsp;and&nbsp;Address of Beneficial Owner</b>
</p>

</td><td rowspan="2" colspan="1" width="133.08661417322838" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt; " valign="bottom">

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>Direct or Indirect </b>
</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>Ownership with </b>
</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>Sole Voting and </b>
</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>Investment&nbsp;Power</b>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(1)	</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left: 20pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">Jim C. Walton has pledged 4,251,488 of the Shares directly owned by him as security for a line of credit extended to a company not affiliated with Walmart. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(2)	</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left: 20pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">This number includes 63,517 Shares held in the 401(k) Plan on behalf of S. Robson Walton. He has sole voting and investment power with respect to these Shares. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(3)	</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left: 20pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">Walton Enterprises, LLC holds a total of 1,609,891,131 Shares. Alice L. Walton, Jim C. Walton and S. Robson Walton share voting and dispositive power with respect to all Shares held by Walton&nbsp;Enterprises, LLC, individually as managing members of Walton Enterprises, LLC, and in their capacities as co-trustees of the John T. Walton Estate Trust, which is also a managing member of Walton Enterprises, LLC. The managing members have the power to sell and vote those Shares. The business address of each managing member is P.O. Box 1508, Bentonville, Arkansas 72712. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(4)	</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left: 20pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">This number includes 39,643,834 Shares held by trusts in which Alice L. Walton, as cotrustee, shares voting and dispositive power with an entity under her control, which have been registered for sale from time to time on a registration statement filed by the company with the SEC on December 8, 2011. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(5)	</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left: 20pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">The number includes 2,174 Shares held by the the John T. Walton Residuary Trust, as to which Jim C. Walton, Alice L. Walton, and an entity under her control, as cotrustees, share voting and dispositive power. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(6)	</p>
<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:2.5pt; padding-left: 20pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">This number includes 1,357,974 Shares held by a partnership as to which Jim C. Walton, as a trustee of a certain trust that is a general partner thereof, shares voting and dispositive power with Alice L. Walton, as a trustee of certain trusts that are general partners thereof, and with certain of their nieces and nephews, the other general partners thereof. </p>

<p align="justify" style="margin: 0pt; margin-bottom:-11.5pt; line-height:11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-style: normal; font-size: 9pt;">(7)	</p>

<a name="_N15D3F"></a>

<p style="margin-top:30pt; margin-bottom:20pt; padding-left:8pt; text-indent:0pt; line-height:28pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:22pt; font-weight:bold">


<font color="#007DC3">Section&nbsp;16(a) Beneficial Ownership Reporting Compliance </font>


</p>

<p style="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:6pt; padding-left: 8.5pt; text-indent: 0pt; line-height:11pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:9pt;" align="justify">Section&nbsp;16(a) of the Exchange Act requires Walmart&rsquo;s directors, Executive Officers, and persons who own more than ten&nbsp;percent of the outstanding Shares to file reports of ownership and changes in ownership with the SEC. SEC regulations require Walmart to identify anyone who failed to file a required report or filed a late report during fiscal 2013. Walmart believes that all Section&nbsp;16(a) filing requirements were met during fiscal 2013. </p>

<p style="margin-top: 0pt; margin-bottom: 3pt; padding-left: 17.2pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="justify"></p>
<p style="margin:0pt; margin-top:14pt; margin-bottom: 14pt; line-height:10pt; font-family:Arial; font-size:8pt;" align="right">

<b>&nbsp;</b>

</td><td rowspan="1" colspan="1" width="143.43307086614178" style="border-bottom:1.5pt solid #000000; padding-right:0pt; " valign="bottom">

</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>price of outstanding </b>
</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">

</p>

</p>

<p style="margin: 0pt; line-height: 11.5pt; font-family: Arial; font-size: 9pt;" align="right">
<b>($)</b>
</p>
